feat(entity): entity-control actions — read/mutate non-player entities by GUID

First implementation slice of the entity-control catalog, on top of the entity
events base. A flow can now inspect and mutate the specific entity an event named.

Foundational (commands.lua):
 - ResolveEntity helper — keys a target by guid (Ents[guid]) OR prefab+x/z+radius
   (TheSim:FindEntities), with the mandatory IsValid guard; returns found:false +
   reason (gone/not_found/bad_args) on a stale/missing GUID, never indexes nil.
 - spawn_prefab / spawn_at_player now RETURN the spawned GUID via a spawn_result
   event when a token is given (the spawn->control->react loop). Fire-and-forget
   spawns without a token are unchanged.

Read:
 - get_entity — resolves a target and emits entity_data with a flat per-component
   object (health/combat/burnable/freezable/workable/fueled/perishable/hunger/
   domesticatable/rideable/container...), present-component detection drives the
   shape. container items capped at 40.

State mutators (each gated on the component being present, pcall-contained):
 - entity_set_health (SetPercent/DoDelta), entity_kill (ForceKill),
   entity_extinguish / entity_ignite (burnable), entity_set_fuel (fueled),
   entity_freeze (AddColdness — the safe path per the spec critic) / entity_unfreeze.

Frontend wiring: 8 entity actions in ACTION_TYPES (each exposes both keying paths),
spawn_result + entity_data as triggerable result events, guid/percent/delta/coldness
added to NUMERIC_PARAM_KEYS. Backend needs no per-action code — runFlowAction
dispatches any action_type as a generic command.

Tests: entity-commands.test.ts runs the REAL core+commands under fengari with
mocked Ents/FindEntities — resolver (guid/pos/stale/unknown), get_entity per-
component shape, every mutator fires the right method + gates on absent component,
spawn-returns-GUID. Plus catalog<->command consistency. 312 pass, tsc clean.

